research-atlas
==============

A normalized, citable graph of the global research economy.

Author:    Gianangelo Dichio
Publisher: bucket-foundation (https://bucket.foundation)
License:   MIT (code) / CC-BY-4.0 (published datasets)

This project generalizes prior private research-landscape work into an open,
source-agnostic atlas of research funding and output.

Data sources retain their own terms; research-atlas stores provenance
(source, source_id, source_url, as_of) on every row so each fact is
attributable to its origin. Source attributions:

  - NSF Award Search API  -- U.S. National Science Foundation (public domain)
  - ROR                   -- Research Organization Registry (CC0)
  - OpenAlex              -- OpenAlex / OurResearch (CC0)        [planned]
  - NIH RePORTER          -- U.S. National Institutes of Health  [planned]
  - CORDIS                -- European Commission (CC-BY)          [planned]

Published datasets are intended to become citable Bucket Foundation canon
artifacts. See docs/ARCHITECTURE.md ("Publish-to-Bucket seam").
